results.name: Number of distinct values obtained when Euler phi (A000010) is applied to proper divisors of n.
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..65537
example: For n = 6, it has three proper divisors: 1, 2, 3, and applying A000010 to these gives 1, 1 and 2, with just two distinct values, thus a(6) = 2.
xref: Cf. also A304793, A305611, A316555, A316556, A319685 for similarly constructed sequences.
results.author: _Antti Karttunen_, Oct 02 2018
